## Chapter 1. Files and Directories

1.1. Print Working Directory:
pwd

1.2. Change Working Directory:
cd 'new directory'

1.3. List Directory Contents:
ls $DIRECTORY

With detailed information:
ls -l

Show hidden files too:
ls -a

1.4. Make directory:
mkdir $DIRECTORY

Make directory and make parents directories if neccessary:
mkdir -p a/b/

1.5. Move or rename files or directories:
mv file1 file2

1.6. Remove empty directory
rmdir dir1

1.7. Remove files or directories
rm -r directory_empty
rm file1 file2 file3
rm -rf directory

1.8. Copy files or directories
cp -r dir1 dir2
cp file1 file2

1.9. Display free disk space
df -h

1.10. Disk Usage
du -sh dir1 file1 dir2

1.11. Check file type
file $FILENAME


